Choppin em up!!! Choppy mofo chop-chops!! Here I am cutting pieces off of the source and prepping em for molding. 
After glueing injection spouts onto the masters I use hot glue and secure the piece on the cardboard mold base…. 

Then I build a box frame around it…. 

I like to leave extra space/silicone at the cut line area so the silicone can use it’s natural rebound properties to create a cleaner/tighter seam line…. 

Part 2 coming tomorrow?  Later today?  I’m just as curious as you are about when the next segment will drop

It’s story time!! BIG RAD WOLF!!! Ever wonder what the backstory is for @slicecityrebels #SCRBIGRADWOLF?  Well you’re in luck!! Take a listen!! Sculpted by @scottthensey, designed in collaboration with @adambartontattoo and painted by @hoarceebu!! If you want to buy one they’re, $230 shipped in the states…. How do ya like his origin story?

“JJ Stryder was a decorated veteran in a past life. Having served more tours to the Middle East and he could remember JJ wanted to escape. He retired to the Santa Cruz mountains for the peaceful solitude he had always been searching for. After becoming one of the areas main top shelf farmers for the cannabis industry, JJ caught the attention of some racist ass rival Peckerwood farmers. They didn’t like to see a black man succeeding, and they would cry themselves to sleep over it. One night during a harvest moon, JJ was cutting down his harvest when Filthy Mikey and the rest of his gang, Hells  Peckers, showed up to murder JJ. Outnumbered, JJ managed to put up a good fight and tear out one of filthy Mikeys eyes, but in the end, JJ fell. Mikey his gang proceeded to drenched the farm in experimental chemicals used for leaving a rival farm barren. JJ‘s blood ran so thick with  agent orange from all the tours in the Middle East that something happened……. Instead of killing JJ, they reacted to the agent orange, and set off a dark mutation!!!! Suddenly, JJ was no more and the Big Rad Wolf had risen!!! Big Rad Wolf made short work of all of Hell’s Peckers, and vowed to take on a new mission… to find and unalive every single racist trash, inbred dork to exist on the Earth…”

“The Rebirth” 
Another oldie from the archives… standing a whole 9” tall and weighing at over 2lbs of resin…. I originally had created this piece in 2015 but never got to use em as originally intended… but in 2019, I gave this guy a proper name n showed em off when still I wasted time with online “art shows”… 
Did a two piece skunk skull for the head, sculpted on some tweakage to the vintage 12” jawa torso and used the V1 Malebolgia for feetsies n hands. 
He didn’t sell, so sooner or later there’s going to be another chance to own em… for the right price 😜
